ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

Overall, how would you rate the RLS discomfort in your legs or arms?
Notes: 0 = None; 1 = Mild; 2 = Moderate; 3 = Severe; 4 = Very severe; -9 = missing/not reported

ElementDescription: Overall, how would you rate the need to move around because of your RLS symptoms?
Notes: 0 = None; 1 = Mild; 2 = Moderate; 3 = Severe; 4 = Very severe; -9 = missing/not reported

ElementDescription: Overall, how much relief of your RLS arm or leg discomfort do you get from moving around?
Notes: 0 = No RLS symptoms to be relieved; 1 = Either complete or almost complete relief; 2 = Moderate relief; 3 = slight relief; 4 = No relief

ElementDescription: Overall, how severe is your sleep disturbance from your RLS symptoms?
Notes: 0 = None; 1 = Mild; 2 = Moderate; 3 = Severe; 4 = Very severe; -9 = missing/not reported

ElementDescription: How severe is your tiredness or sleepiness from your RLS symptoms?
Notes: 0 = None; 1 = Mild; 2 = Moderate; 3 = Severe; 4 = Very severe; -9 = missing/not reported

ElementDescription: Overall, how severe is your RLS as a whole?
Notes: 0 = None; 1 = Mild; 2 = Moderate; 3 = Severe; 4 = Very severe; -9 = missing/not reported

ElementDescription: How often do you get RLS symptoms?
Notes: 0 = None; 1 = Mild (1 day in 1 week); 2 = Moderate (2-3 days in 1 week); 3 = Severe (4-5 days in 1 week); 4 = Very severe (6-7 days in 1 week); -9 = missing/not reported

ElementDescription: When you have RLS symptoms, how severe are they on an average day?
Notes: 0 = None; 1 = Mild (less than 1 h per 24h); 2 = Moderate (1-3 h per 24h); 3 = Severe (3-8 h per 24h); 4 = Very severe (8 h or more per 24 h); -9 = missing/not reported

ElementDescription: Overall, how severe is the impact of your RLS symptoms on your ability to carry out your daily affairs, for example carrying out a satisfactory family, home, social, school, or work life?
Notes: 0 = None; 1 = Mild; 2 = Moderate; 3 = Severe; 4 = Very severe; -9 = missing/not reported

ElementDescription: How severe is your mood disturbance from your RLS symptoms - for example angry, depressed, sad, anxious, or irritable?
Notes: 0 = None; 1 = Mild; 2 = Moderate; 3 = Severe; 4 = Very severe; -9 = missing/not reported

ElementDescription: Rating that the participant gave on their symptom severity for the preceding week overall
Notes: 1 or 2 = Mild; 3 or 4 = Moderate; 5 or 6 = Severe; 7 or 8 = Very severe; -9 = missing/not reported

ElementDescription: RLS Total Score
Notes: Add scores from all questions; 0 to 10 = Mild; 11 to 20 = Moderate; 21 to 30 = Severe; 31 to 40 = Very Severe
